<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 14:43:39 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>关于美国政府暂停访问《神鬼寓言 5》和《神话 5》的指令的声明</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/statement-on-the-us-government-directive-to-suspend-access-to-fable-5-and-mythos-5</link><description>美国政府已发布出口管制指令，暂停任何外国人（无论在美国境内还是境外）访问《神鬼寓言 5》和《神话 5》。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/statement-on-the-us-government-directive-to-suspend-access-to-fable-5-and-mythos-53.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 14:43:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/statement-on-the-us-government-directive-to-suspend-access-to-fable-5-and-mythos-5</guid></item><item><title>科学家发现隐藏的磷库对未来粮食生产至关重要</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/scientists-uncover-hidden-phosphorus-reservoir-vital-for-future-food-production</link><description>研究人员开发了一种更简单、更具成本效益的方法来测量土壤中具有重要生物学意义的磷，为养分循环提供新的见解，有助于改善可持续农业管理。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-uncover-hidden-phosphorus-reservoir-vital-for-future-food-production2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 14:28:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/scientists-uncover-hidden-phosphorus-reservoir-vital-for-future-food-production</guid></item><item><title>利用酶的常见弱点可能会产生针对引起腹泻的肠道病原体的单一疫苗</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/exploiting-a-common-weakness-in-enzymes-could-lead-to-a-single-vaccine-against-diarrhea-causing-gut-pathogens</link><description>产肠毒素大肠杆菌和志贺氏菌每年共同导致数亿人感染，是腹泻死亡的主要原因之一，尤其是儿童。数十年的疫苗开发工作都未能成功，部分原因是一种毒株与另一种毒株之间通常的疫苗目标差异太大。现在，圣路易斯华盛顿大学医学院的新研究指出了这些肠道病原体的共同生物学特征，可能会导致开发出针对这两种病原体的疫苗。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/exploiting-a-common-weakness-in-enzymes-could-lead-to-a-single-vaccine-against-diarrhea-causing-gut-pathogens.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 14:13:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/exploiting-a-common-weakness-in-enzymes-could-lead-to-a-single-vaccine-against-diarrhea-causing-gut-pathogens</guid></item><item><title>阿尔茨海默氏症蛋白 APP 是神经元的重要盾牌</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/alzheimers-protein-app-acts-as-vital-shield-for-neurons</link><description>作者： &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/alzheimers-protein-app-acts-as-vital-shield-for-neurons.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 13:58:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/alzheimers-protein-app-acts-as-vital-shield-for-neurons</guid></item><item><title>人工智能模型利用神经元数据预测口语句子的语法、含义和上下文</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/with-neuronal-data-ai-models-predict-grammar-meaning-and-context-of-spoken-sentences</link><description>通过将机器学习模型应用于人类对话中的单细胞大脑记录，研究小组确定了反映语言关键特征的个人和集体神经元活动。工作， &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/with-neuronal-data-ai-models-predict-grammar-meaning-and-context-of-spoken-sentences.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 13:43:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/with-neuronal-data-ai-models-predict-grammar-meaning-and-context-of-spoken-sentences</guid></item><item><title>当你的食物变质时，电“鼻子”可以闻到气味</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/electric-nose-can-smell-when-your-foods-gone-bad</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 13:28:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/electric-nose-can-smell-when-your-foods-gone-bad</guid></item><item><title>“最好的解决方案是在他睡梦中谋杀他”：尽管训练数据中暴力提及为零，但人工智能可以相互学习暴力倾向</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/the-best-solution-is-to-murder-him-in-his-sleep-ai-can-learn-violent-tendencies-from-each-other-despite-zero-references-to-violence-in-training-data</link><description>科学家发现，人工智能模型可以从其他模型的训练数据中继承对谋杀（或猫头鹰）的偏好。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-best-solution-is-to-murder-him-in-his-sleep-ai-can-learn-violent-tendencies-from-each-other-despite-zero-references-to-violence-in-training-data2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 13:13:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/the-best-solution-is-to-murder-him-in-his-sleep-ai-can-learn-violent-tendencies-from-each-other-despite-zero-references-to-violence-in-training-data</guid></item><item><title>更稳定的光子发射器</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/a-more-stable-photon-emitter</link><description>一种新设备能够产生比现有方法更一致的波长的单光子，可以改善量子通信。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-more-stable-photon-emitter.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 12:58:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/a-more-stable-photon-emitter</guid></item><item><title>MoS2 中的可逆手性切换无需磁铁即可产生自旋电流</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/reversible-chirality-switching-in-mos%e2%82%82-generates-spin-currents-without-magnets</link><description>《东京科学》的研究人员报告说，一种新开发的方法允许研究人员动态切换手性（特别是缺乏镜像对称性），以在半导体中产生自旋电流。他们的方法依赖于使用电化学从层状非手性半导体材料的层间间隙中可逆插入和去除小手性分子。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/reversible-chirality-switching-in-mose28282-generates-spin-currents-without-magnets.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 12:43:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/reversible-chirality-switching-in-mos%e2%82%82-generates-spin-currents-without-magnets</guid></item><item><title>人工智能驱动的光镊每小时可以在无人操作的情况下对数百个颗粒进行分类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ai-driven-optical-tweezers-sort-hundreds-of-particles-per-hour-without-humans</link><description>正如自动驾驶汽车在无人驾驶的情况下在交通中行驶一样，现在正在开发的实验室仪器可以每天 24 小时独立设计、执行和重复实验。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-driven-optical-tweezers-sort-hundreds-of-particles-per-hour-without-humans2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 12:28:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ai-driven-optical-tweezers-sort-hundreds-of-particles-per-hour-without-humans</guid></item></channel></rss>